Product name: 30% OFF SALE with free resizing!! Lost Treasure 1ct DBlock Tanzanite 10kt Yellow Gold Mens Ring
Description:
Here we have for purchase or layaway a like new slightly used Glowing Treasure 1ct Tanzanite 10kt Yellow Gold Mens Ring. This mesmerizing intense bluish violet round cut natural Tanzanite has outstanding fire. The stone measures 7.15x3.06mm and weighs 1 carat. This exquisite D'Block glowing bluish violet color is most valuable and rare in the gemstone industry. Pictures are magnified 50x to show detail and are not visible to the naked eye. This amazing high quality gemstone is set in a very detailed solid 10kt Yellow Gold nugget style 6-prong setting and is clearly marked 10k. The ring weighs 16.6 grams and is a easily re-sizable size 14. These stones were named by Tiffany & Co after Tanzania, the country it was discovered. Tanzanites are noted for its remarkably strong trichroism, appearing alternately sapphire blue, violet and burgundy depending on the crystal orientation. They also appear differently when viewed under alternate lighting conditions. The blues appear more evident when subjected to fluorescent light and the violet hues can be seen readily when viewed under incandescent illumination. This ring is a bold statement piece and looks great on the hand. This high end ring is well crafted and very detailed with the nugget design. D'block Tanzanites are impossible to find and only the best. ADDITIONAL 7 PICTURES AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST!! Comes shipped in an exquisite brand new natural redwood and leather ring box.

Product name: Original Vintage 1941 JohnJames Audubon Birds of America Bookplate Print Bird Print 311 White Pelican 312 Old Squaw
Description:
Offered is an  ORIGINAL ( NOT a 1.00 REPRODUCTION) Vintage 1941 John James Audubon Book Plate, Print, or Bird Print
No.      311   White Pelican        and/or            No.  312     Old Squaw
Note:  
These bookplates, prints, or pages are two (2) sided.  In other words, there is a bird print on each side.  You can decide which side to display when you frame the print.  The prints do not show through when framed.
I am  pleased to offer my very large collection/inventory of prints, bookplates, bird prints, or Ornithological Prints of done by John James Audubon for his work," Birds of America.  I have removed or cut these prints from the books in which they were published.  These are NOT "art print" reproductions.
The books were published in 1941.  I have several of these books.  I did antique shows all over the US for many years. I also had an antique shop.  I sold these prints like crazy at antique shows and in my antique shop.  But I still have many left, (I bought a lot of books!).  I am offering these prints at a great price.  MUCH less than I sold them for at shows and my shop.
The prints measure about  8" to 8 1/2"  by 12".
NOTE: 
If you order more than one (1) bookplate or print, the bookplates or prints will probably not be the same size or have the same age  toning, as they will come from different books.  The books age and tone differently depending on the elements to which they were exposed.  Also, the books were manually cut.  
These bookplates or prints are all in very good condition.  However, ALL of these bookplates or prints have age toning or yellowing.  This is inevitable with these old prints.  The paper they used for Audubon's "Birds of America" was good paper but it was not top of the line.  These books were made to be affordable for the middle class.  Thus, they all have toning.  A few bookplates or prints may also have some small faint spots.  This is foxing and is common with age.
These bookplates or prints are beautiful framed.  You can have them matted or not.  Many, but not all of these plates will work in 8" x 10" frames.  BUT, you will NOT be able to see or display the name and description.  This is a matter of preference.  I have several framed Audubons in my home.  I have some in  8 x 10's and some that are matted and framed in larger frames.  Up to you.
Sales Tax of 8.25% applies to Texas Residents.
Please email with any questions.
These bookplates or prints will be mailed USPS 1st Class Mail with cardboard reinforcement.
I will ship my Audubons to the  US ONLY!

Product name: Circa 1910 Empire Style Hair Comb
Description:
The “Second Empire” style was made popular by Napoleon III’s reign in France (1852-1870), but its influence lasted for many years after 1870. This comb is a really beautiful example of this lasting influence with its curved shape and Renaissance Revival design. The repousse brass work is gorgeous with garlands and lions making a surprisingly elegant juxtaposition. The blue, pressed-glass accents are an interesting touch, pulling this piece into the turn of the century with its fake hieroglyphs. The blue glass bits and machine stamped brass are very much Czechoslovakian in style. The hair comb is molded celluloid made to imitate tortoise shell.

Product name: Dried Lavender Bouquets
Description:
Our dried lavender bouquets of approximately 125 stems, will spruce up any space while adding a hint of lavender fragrance. No maintenance necessary!
The French lavender has a stronger, woodsy lavender aroma like you would associate with soaps and perfumes.  These bouquets measure 16-20 inches long with a crown of 8 inches. The  buds are a light lavender color.  (photos 1 & 2)

Our Certified Naturally Grown lavender is hand harvested fresh from our field in the morning hours after the dew has dried. This method insures we can meticulously capture the lavender at it's peak beauty and aroma. We hang and store these bundles in a protected environment in order to deliver top notch quality to our customers.
Our lavender is grown in the beautiful foothills of Northern Colorado. We have two plots, with roughly 300 plants in each, and distill our own essential oil. Growing lavender has been a passion for us since 2009, and we now boast 30 different varieties. Our market garden is a tribute to the memory of our parents, who were agriculturalists in Colorado and Kansas. We try to do things the old-fashioned way, just how our forefathers did.

Product name: Sari Silk Ribbon in Dyeable Bone Ivory
Description:
Sari silk yarn is a fun super bulky fiber that is extremely versatile. People use it for knitting, crochet, tapestries, rugs, weaving, and jewelry making to name a few activities. To make this yarn, women in India tear silk saris into quarter-inch strips by hand and then sew the strips together. This work provides jobs for women so that they, in turn, can provide for their families. 
Sari silk can be used for crochet and knit projects, dyeing, weaving, tapestry, jewelry making, wrapping gifts and anything else your imagination can dream up.
Size: 100 grams/60 yards
Weight: Super Bulky - 6
Gauge: 3 - 4/ 1 -2 stitches per inch
Needle/Hook Size: 11 and up/ L and up.
Care: Hand wash in cold water, lay flat to dry or dry clean
Physical Quality: Varying textures and widths of ribbon, no elasticity, lovely color variety

Product name: British Suede and Lambswool Handmade Moccasin Slippers
Description:
Sheepland Ltd is our family run sheepskin business, we've been lovingly handcrafting our Slippers and accessories in our Somerset Workshop since 1986, which enjoys views of Glastonbury Tor. We pride ourselves on using British materials, e.g. British wool and sheepskin as much as possible to keep this traditional industry alive. These suede and lambswool Moccasins are still made by hand using the traditional methods right here in Somerset. The lining is a wool lining, which is literally sheared from the sheep in the Spring and is later affixed to a backing fabric, which means it is much less expensive then whole sheepskin. The wool lining is natural undyed wool and gives a cosy inside which will keep you warm throughout the Winter months. These Suede Moccasins can be made without a sole (soft sole) or with a firm rubber sole to allow you to pop outside if need be. We would recommend ordering your usual size, if you are a half size we would suggest ordering up a size. These Suede Moccasins are perfect for all the family, without the price tag of pure sheepskin, these wool lined Moccasins really are the next best thing.
When ordering please include your phone number and the foot size (US/UK/EU) these slippers are required for in the notes section. This is to ensure we make and send the correct item ASAP. We will never share your information with anyone.
